      <emotional-journey>
        <reasoning>POV emotional state: The narrator (Kira) cycles from high alert and anxiety into a surprising, scared-but-energized empowerment, then into exhausted relief. At first she’s tense and nervous because the hostile plants have learned and are coordinating—the assault is immediate, multi-directional, and the facility trembles. That anxiety is amplified by Runner’s injury and the apparent failure of Florence’s initial tactic. When the group improvises a collective plan and everyone contributes, Kira experiences an empowering lift: fear remains, but it's reshaped into active agency and fragile trust as the group acts together. After the command node is forced up and destroyed she feels relieved, proud, and quietly moved by the emergent cooperation. Reader experience: The passage is designed to put the reader through a rollercoaster of suspense (real, close danger) into tactical exhilaration (the clever gambit) and cathartic release (victory and the emotional repair). There are multiple beats rather than a single tone: acute tension/dread, then an empowerment/belonging surge, and finally relief/acceptance. Compared to the story so far, this continues the recurring threat→coordination→acceptance arc but importantly reframes it: earlier sequences emphasized fractured trust, Florence’s authority, and paralysis; here the group shifts from relying on a single planner to collective improvisation. Emotionally, the pattern is familiar (danger then teamwork) but it advances the arc by converting lingering betrayal into pragmatic, trust-based cooperation—so the repetition serves growth rather than redundancy.</reasoning>
        <beats>
          <beat tags="tension, dread">POV: Immediate alarm and fear as the attack begins—bioluminescent coordination, multiple assaults, and Runner's injury create acute danger; Kira is watching, physically tense and worried (Scout pressed to her). Reader: Feels breathless suspense and anxiety, keyed to concrete sensory details (shuddering facility, failed barriers, Runner's torn vines). This is a continuation of the story's established high-stakes threat beats.</beat>
          <beat tags="hope, belonging">POV: A surge of fearful-but-energized hope as the group improvises a collective strategy—Kira feels empowered by being part of a shared decision and witnesses plants coordinating in a new, cooperative way; this produces a fragile sense of belonging despite previous betrayals. Reader: Experiences uplifted engagement and moral satisfaction as disparate characters contribute and trust one another enough to attempt a risky, collaborative gambit. This beat shifts the recurring pattern from fractured command to emergent teamwork.</beat>
          <beat tags="relief, acceptance">POV: Exhausted, stunned relief and weary acceptance after the command node is destroyed—the immediate danger is over, bodies and systems are wrecked, and Kira registers the small, imperfect repair of trust ('we can work together'). Reader: Feels cathartic release and warm satisfaction at the victory and the emotional payoff (partial reconciliation and genuine cooperation). Pattern note: The passage resolves tension in a familiar way but with a meaningful emotional advance—trust rebuilt enough to act together—preventing the sequence from feeling merely repetitive.</beat>
